{
  "stem": "16106.6",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They left me in a place, the German-- I think the kids can come-- [INAUDIBLE], I-- I met some people from my camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I met Mike, the cook from Kaiserwald, who told me that his son got killed, got shot while try to escape, that young son of his.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Jacob ?] was shot, that [INAUDIBLE] was shot, that [INAUDIBLE] was shot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "All of them were shot trying to escape.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He was there all alone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I met people who were Jewish girls whom I knew from Kaiswerwald.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "There was a girl from Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And that was my choice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I had to either go back home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "That was Russia, Latvia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And I didn't know if my parents or anybody is alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Or I want to stay in the west.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I mean, I had this idea about-- about the Dane.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Maybe I stay Danish or something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fanny ?] [INAUDIBLE] came from Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said to me, why don't you pretend coming from Leipzig, Germany?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Leipzig, the Jews were in the fur business, which was called in German [GERMAN], which was a really an in name.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I thought [GERMAN] has to do with smoking.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the guy was writing out, where are you from-- from Leipzig?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What did your parents do?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "As I said, they [GERMAN], they had cigarettes to sell.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, that gave me almost away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he-- he-- he just winked at me, and I didn't have to go to-- back to the Russian zone.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And well, I go-- I have [INAUDIBLE] those ladies from-- from my camp, [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Fanny, ?] and [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Rosel ?] and [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rosel's-- ?] I think [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Rosel's ?] husband showed up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I got-- as they sent me off to the office, to [INAUDIBLE] office, [?",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
